# Frontend Setup (Angular) — Polymarket BTC 15m Bot

## Goal
Build a clean Angular UI that shows bot status, recent signals, and trades, with a lightweight local API as the data source.

## Architecture
- Backend bot (in `backend/`)
- Local API service (new, small FastAPI or Flask)
- Angular frontend (new)

## What The Frontend Should Include
- Status panel
- Current mode: `SIMULATION` or `LIVE`
- Connection status to Polymarket
- Last tick time
- Current market and token prices (Up/Down)
- Recent signals (direction, score, confidence, reason)
- Recent trades (paper + live)
- Paper trades list from `backend/paper_trades.json`
- Account balance (USDC.e)
- Orders list (open, filled, rejected)
- Error/Warning log feed
- Controls
- Start/Stop bot
- Toggle simulation/live
- Refresh credentials

## Data Endpoints (API)
- `GET /status`
- `GET /market`
- `GET /signals`
- `GET /trades`
- `GET /paper-trades`
- `GET /orders`
- `GET /logs`

## Angular Project Setup
```
ng new frontend
cd frontend
ng serve
```

## UI Layout
- Top bar: bot status, mode, connection
- Left column: market data, signals
- Right column: trades, orders
- Bottom: logs

## Suggested Components
- `StatusCardComponent`
- `MarketCardComponent`
- `SignalListComponent`
- `TradeTableComponent`
- `OrderTableComponent`
- `LogFeedComponent`
- `ControlsComponent`

## Data Refresh
- Poll API every 3–5 seconds
- Use Angular `HttpClient`
- Optional: WebSocket for logs later

## Security Notes
- Never expose private keys or API secrets in frontend
- Keep API bound to localhost unless you add auth

